It is an idea that has been applied.
Brazil has adopted a forward-thinking approach, and over 2,000 Syrians have obtained humanitarian visas, traveled to Brazil, and upon arrival, applied for refugee status.
In this setup, every Syrian who did this was granted refugee status and recognized as a refugee.
There is a historical precedent.
Between 1922 and 1942, these Nansen passports were used as travel documents allowing 450,000 Assyrians, Turks, and Chechens to travel to Europe and apply for refugee status elsewhere in Europe.
And the Nansen International Office for Refugees was awarded the Nobel Peace Prize in recognition of this viable strategy.
